This paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with limited feedback MIMO communication systems and codebook design. It may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it involves channel state information (CSI) and communication systems. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as clustering algorithms are used to analyze the data. The paper also mentions the use of K-means clustering, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new codebook design, which could be considered as an application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
